The platform''s development entity, Baton Corporation Ltd (UK-registered), has expanded aggressively beyond its core launchpad. In March 2025, Pump.fun launched PumpSwap, its own native DEX (AMM similar to Uniswap V2), replacing Raydium as the destination for graduated tokens and eliminating migration fees. The team acquired Padre (October 2025, rebranded as Terminal) and Vyper (February 2026) to build cross-chain trading capabilities spanning Solana, Ethereum, Base, and BNB Smart Chain. In July 2025, Pump.fun conducted one of the largest ICOs in crypto history, raising approximately $1.2 billion ($500M public sale in 12 minutes + ~$700M private sale) for its PUMP governance token at a $4 billion fully diluted valuation.

Despite facing regulatory scrutiny (FCA warning, RICO class action lawsuits in SDNY), growing competition from LetsBonk and LaunchLab, and revenue declining ~77% from peak levels, Pump.fun continues to generate significant revenue. The team is investing in mobile apps, creator revenue sharing, and the Glass Full Foundation liquidity program to sustain its ecosystem.', 'Crypto / Web3', 'Infrastructure', 'Liquid Token', 'July 12, 2025: PUMP Token ICO — public sale raised ~$500M in 12 minutes (125 billion tokens at $0.004/token, 12.5% of total supply). Private sale raised ~$700M (18% of supply at same price). Total raised approximately $1.2 billion. FDV at ICO was $4 billion. Total supply: 1 trillion PUMP tokens. Allocation: 33% ICO (18% private, ~12.5% public), 24% community, 20% team, 13% existing investors, remainder to ecosystem/foundation/liquidity. As of early 2026, PUMP trades below ICO price at ~$0.002 with ~$1.2 billion market cap.', 'Pump.fun pioneered the Solana memecoin launchpad category and remains the dominant player, though competition has intensified. Key competitors include: (1) LetsBonk.fun — Solana-based challenger that briefly surpassed Pump.fun in daily token launches around July 2025, differentiated by BONK buyback program; (2) LaunchLab — Raydium-backed competitor launched as a direct response to PumpSwap; (3) Believe — social media-integrated launchpad gaining market share. On the DEX side, PumpSwap competes with Raydium, Jupiter, and other Solana DEXes. Pump.fun''s moat includes brand recognition, massive user base, network effects, and expanding product suite (Terminal, mobile app).', 'https://x.com/Pumpfun', 'in_diligence', '{Memecoin,Solana,"Token Launchpad",DEX,DeFi,"Liquid Token"}', NULL, '2026-03-21 20:29:45.727433', 'https://pump.fun', '', 'https://x.com/pumpdotfun', '', '1e9bf641-c93c-4629-906a-f50db9050164', 'Token Launchpad / DEX', 0, NULL, NULL, '[{"title":"The Memecoin Phenomenon: An In-Depth Study of Solana''s Blockchain Trends (arXiv, Dec 2025)","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.11850","source":"arXiv","relevance":"Peer-reviewed empirical study analyzing Pump.fun''s Q4 2024 on-chain data, finding it minted 71.1% of all Solana tokens yet fewer than 2% graduated to DEXs — essential for assessing sustainability of the launchpad model''s revenue base."},{"title":"SEC Division of Corporation Finance: Staff Statement on Meme Coins (Feb 27, 2025)","url":"https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/speeches-statements/staff-statement-meme-coins","source":"SEC.gov","relevance":"The SEC''s official staff guidance that memecoins generally are not securities under federal law — a critical legal defense for Pump.fun''s SDNY RICO lawsuit but notably non-binding and contested by Commissioner Crenshaw, making regulatory risk assessment essential."},{"title":"FCA CP25/40: Regulating Cryptoasset Activities — UK Crypto Regulatory Framework (Dec 2025)","url":"https://www.fca.org.uk/publications/consultation-papers/cp25-40-regulating-cryptoasset-activities","source":"UK Financial Conduct Authority (FCA)","relevance":"As Pump.fun''s parent Baton Corporation is UK-registered, this FCA consultation paper defining the comprehensive new UK cryptoasset regime (effective Oct 2027) directly determines future compliance obligations for trading platforms, DeFi, and token launches."},{"title":"Uniswap V2 Core Whitepaper — Constant Product AMM Design","url":"https://app.uniswap.org/whitepaper.pdf","source":"Uniswap","relevance":"PumpSwap''s AMM is explicitly modeled on the Uniswap V2 constant-product formula (x·y=k); this foundational whitepaper is essential for evaluating PumpSwap''s technical design, fee mechanics, and competitive positioning against more capital-efficient AMMs."},{"title":"Solana''s Proprietary AMM Revolution — Helius Research Deep-Dive (Oct 2025)","url":"https://www.helius.dev/blog/solanas-proprietary-amm-revolution","source":"Helius (Solana infrastructure provider)","relevance":"Proprietary AMMs now capture 60%+ of Solana DEX volume on liquid pairs, fundamentally restructuring the competitive landscape; this analysis explains why PumpSwap''s passive-AMM model is being squeezed to long-tail memecoin assets only, directly impacting revenue potential."}]', true, 'Tier 2', 'PUMP', 'pumpCmXqMfrsAkQ5r49WcJnRayYRqmXz6ae8H7H9Dfn', 'solana', NULL) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.companies (id, name, one_liner, description, sector, business_model, stage, funding_history, competitive_landscape, source_url, pipeline_stage, tags, image_url, created_at, website_url, github_url, twitter_url, linkedin_url, user_id, sub_sector, deleted_report_count, excitement_score, excitement_reason, adjacent_reads, has_liquid_token, token_tier, token_ticker, token_contract_address, token_chain, liquid_token_analysis) VALUES ('31c55d15-5647-49b9-ac6d-7d88a348e66b', 'Hyperliquid', 'A high-performance Layer 1 blockchain and decentralized exchange specializing in perpetual futures trading with fully on-chain order books and sub-second finality.', 'Hyperliquid is a custom-built Layer 1 blockchain and decentralized exchange that has become a dominant platform in decentralized perpetual futures trading. Built from the ground up by a small team with no venture capital funding, the platform supports up to 200,000 orders per second with sub-second finality via its custom HyperBFT consensus mechanism. Its architecture splits into HyperCore (handling on-chain perpetual futures and spot order books) and HyperEVM (providing Ethereum-compatible smart contract functionality), enabling a unified ecosystem where trading, DeFi apps, and token launches coexist on the same chain.

Hyperliquid commands approximately 70% or more of the decentralized perpetuals market and has processed trillions of dollars in cumulative volume since launch in 2023. The platform offers leverage across 145+ markets with zero gas fees, a fully on-chain order book, and a trading experience that rivals centralized exchanges. Its HYPE token, launched via a community airdrop on November 29, 2024 with 31% going directly to users and zero VC allocation, has achieved a market cap in the range of $9.5–10 billion and ranks in the top 15 cryptocurrencies. The platform generates substantial revenue, with 97% of protocol fees directed toward HYPE buybacks and burns.

Founded by Jeff Yan, a Harvard-educated former quantitative trader at Hudson River Trading, Hyperliquid was entirely bootstrapped using profits from Yan''s prior crypto market-making firm, Chameleon Trading. The deliberate rejection of VC funding has become a core part of the project''s identity. The team of 11 is primarily based in Singapore and was expanding to 14 members as of late 2025. Hyperliquid was named Decrypt''s 2025 Project of the Year and Jeff Yan was recognized in CoinDesk''s Most Influential 2025 list.', 'Crypto / Web3', 'Infrastructure', 'Liquid Token', 'Hyperliquid is entirely self-funded/bootstrapped. Jeff Yan funded the project using profits from his prior crypto market-making firm, Chameleon Trading. The project has never raised venture capital funding. Co-founder iliensinc confirmed on Discord that Hyperliquid has never conducted any external financing. The HYPE token launched November 29, 2024 via community airdrop — 31% to users, 38.88% future community rewards, 23.8% core contributors, 6% foundation, 0.3% community grants, 0.012% protocol upgrades. As of March 2026, HYPE trades at approximately $39–40 with a market cap of approximately $9.5–10B and FDV of approximately $38B.', 'Hyperliquid is the dominant decentralized perpetual futures exchange, commanding approximately 70%+ of DEX perp market share as of mid-2025. Key competitors include: (1) dYdX — a former market leader now on its own Cosmos-based chain; (2) GMX — AMM-based perpetuals on Arbitrum/Avalanche; (3) Jupiter — Solana-based perp DEX that rose to prominence in late 2024; (4) Vertex Protocol — Arbitrum-based hybrid orderbook/AMM; (5) Lighter — an Ethereum-based ZK rollup perp DEX that raised $68M led by Founders Fund and Ribbit Capital at a $1.5B valuation, with participation from Haun Ventures and Robinhood; (6) Aevo — offers crypto options in addition to perps; (7) Aster DEX — a Hyperliquid competitor closely aligned with Binance; (8) EdgeX. Hyperliquid also indirectly competes with centralized exchanges like Binance and Bybit.', 'https://x.com/HyperliquidX', 'invested', '{DeFi,"Layer 1",DEX,"On-chain Order Book","Liquid Token"}', NULL, '2026-03-21 11:40:04.467956', 'https://hyperliquid.xyz', 'https://github.com/hyperliquid-dex', 'https://x.com/HyperliquidX', '', '1e9bf641-c93c-4629-906a-f50db9050164', 'Perpetuals/Derivatives', 0, 10, 'Hyperliquid', '[{"title":"HotStuff: BFT Consensus with Linearity and Responsiveness (Yin et al., 2019)","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.05069","source":"arXiv / ACM PODC 2019","relevance":"HyperBFT is directly derived from the HotStuff protocol; this seminal paper defines the theoretical foundations, security guarantees, and performance properties (linear communication complexity, optimistic responsiveness) that underpin Hyperliquid''s consensus layer and its claimed 200K orders/second throughput."},{"title":"CFTC Chairman Selig: ''The Next Phase of Project Crypto: Unleashing Innovation for the New Frontier of Finance''","url":"https://www.cftc.gov/PressRoom/SpeechesTestimony/opaselig1","source":"CFTC (Official Speech, January 29, 2026)","relevance":"The CFTC Chairman''s directive to onshore perpetual futures and create safe harbors for DeFi developers represents the most consequential regulatory development for Hyperliquid — a policy shift that could either unlock massive U.S. institutional volume or impose leverage caps and compliance requirements that challenge its offshore-centric model."},{"title":"DEX Appeal: The Rise of Decentralized Exchanges","url":"https://research.grayscale.com/reports/dex-appeal-the-rise-of-decentralized-exchanges","source":"Grayscale Research (June 2025)","relevance":"This institutional-grade market analysis quantifies the DEX-vs-CEX fee structure, volume share dynamics, and competitive positioning of Hyperliquid against both centralized and decentralized rivals — essential for validating the total addressable market thesis and fee compression risk."},{"title":"Hyperliquid Bridge Smart Contract Audit Reports by Zellic (August 2023 & November 2023)","url":"https://github.com/Zellic/publications/blob/master/Hyperliquid%20-%20Zellic%20Audit%20Report.pdf","source":"Zellic / GitHub","relevance":"The only independent security audits of Hyperliquid cover only the bridge contract (not the core L1 or DEX logic); the audit flagged issues like incorrect finalization checks and signature reuse, and the bridge''s ~200-second dispute window securing ~$4B in user funds represents a critical infrastructure risk that investors must independently assess."},{"title":"How Perp DEXs Quietly Took Over 26% of the Futures Market (HTX Research Report)","url":"https://cointelegraph.com/research/how-perp-dexs-quietly-took-over-26-of-the-futures-market","source":"Cointelegraph Research / HTX Research (November 2025)","relevance":"This comprehensive competitive landscape report documents the evolution from AMM to CLOB-based perpetual DEX models, Hyperliquid''s market share peak and subsequent decline from 73% to ~32% as competitors like Aster and Lighter emerged with aggressive incentives — critical for assessing the durability of Hyperliquid''s dominance and the sustainability of its moat."}]', true, 'Tier 1', 'HYPE', '', 'hyperliquid', '

