| **Fair distribution (25–45% initial float)?** | ✅ Yes — 31% genesis airdrop at TGE, zero VC allocation |
| **Downgrade triggers?** | 🟡 Validator centralization (81% of stake controlled by protocol) and JELLY exploit response raise governance concerns; revenue cyclicality flagged |

**Rationale:** Hyperliquid is a rare protocol that combines dominant market share (~70% of perp DEX volume), substantial and growing real revenue (~$844M in 2025), an aggressive buyback-and-burn mechanism channeling nearly all fees back to token holders, and a structurally clean distribution with zero VC allocation. The 31% genesis airdrop falls squarely in the "fair" range. Revenue growth and value accrual are clearly Tier 1, though the protocol''s demonstrated willingness to intervene centrally during the JELLY exploit (March 2025) and the 81% validator stake concentration introduce governance risks that prevent an argument for Tier 0. The cyclicality of trading revenue (fees down 56% from peaks) also warrants monitoring but does not negate the structural strength.

