## Executive Summary

PredictParity, branded as "Parity," is a pre-launch prediction market aggregator that aims to provide a unified interface for trading, tracking, and analyzing prediction markets across multiple platforms such as Polymarket and Kalshi. The platform''s stated value proposition is to let users "trade prediction markets across platforms," "track top traders, analyze market data, and make informed decisions." The company is led by a pseudonymous founder known as "MovieTime" (@MovieTimeDev), who has built a following in the prediction markets community but whose real identity and professional background remain unknown. As of the latest available data, the @PredictParity Twitter account was created in September 2025, has 2,860 followers, and has not posted any content. The profile explicitly states "NO COIN," distancing from token-based models.

The prediction market industry represents a massive and rapidly growing addressable market. Total notional trading volume across prediction markets reached over $44 billion in 2025. Kalshi raised $1 billion at an $11 billion valuation in December 2025, while Polymarket received a $2 billion strategic investment from Intercontinental Exchange at a $9 billion post-money valuation. An aggregator layer that unifies access to these fragmented venues addresses a real pain point — but PredictParity enters this race in a pre-product state while at least half a dozen funded competitors are already shipping. No funding, no product, no team details, and no public roadmap have been disclosed. This is a concept-stage opportunity at the earliest possible diligence threshold.

