### Key Metric to Watch

**Crusades MFU progression** is the single most important near-term metric. If the competitive optimization system continues driving MFU higher (currently 66%, approaching centralized datacenter-level efficiency), it validates the core thesis that decentralized training can close the performance gap through crowdsourced optimization rather than centralized R&D spend. The second key metric is **time-to-revenue** from the planned training API services — the project must generate real demand before TAO emissions decline further through halving cycles.', 'complete', '2026-03-13 08:57:25.047274') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
